            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </activity>
    <p xml:id="auto_3973nimt">
        <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Key Takeaway}}</m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_p76g3hm7">
        <m>\text{Velocity}</m> is Speed in a specified direction or the rate of change of displacement with time.
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_aq99sptr">
        Symbol of velocity is given as <m>\textbf{v}</m> while speed is given as <m>\textbf{s}</m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_rgzq9lau">
        <m> v = \frac{\textbf{d}}{\textbf{t}} </m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_nji9o7w9">
        where <m>\textbf{d}</m> represents the distance and <m>\textbf{t}</m> represents time
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_jq1dsh3y">
        For motion with <m>\textbf{constant velocity}</m>, the equation is 
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_nwym29tn">
        <md>
            <mrow> \textbf{s = vt} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_kgafqi3n">
        where <m>\textbf{v}</m> is velocity , <m>\textbf{t}</m> is time and <m>\textbf{s}</m> is displacement
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_y5pm1rel">
        <m>\text{Acceleration}</m> - The rate of change of velocity with time. SI unit is <m>m/s²</m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_dfrmr3em">
        Acceleration is given by
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_1tt260ir">
        <md>
            <mrow>\textbf{Acceleration} \, = \frac{\textbf{Change in velocity}}{\textbf{Time Taken}} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_ouylhuil">
        <md>
            <mrow> a = \frac{\Delta v}{\Delta t} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_x6rw3id1">
        
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_b7mw6hk6">
        Negative acceleration is called <m>\text{ ( deceleration or retardation)}</m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_5a2ntn7r">
        For motion with <m>\textbf{constant acceleration}</m>, the three equations of motion are:
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_3kfvzhfb">
        <ol xml:id="auto_pmgr2vyf" marker="i).">
            <li xml:id="auto_eoxk5bo5">
                <p xml:id="auto_dkk07fpc">
                    <m>\text{final velocity}</m> = Initial velocity + (acceleration <m> \times </m> time)
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_d5yhnoma">
                    <m> \text{v = u + at} </m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_tt4elbrs"> where;
                    <ul xml:id="auto_lt53oxrt">
                        <li xml:id="auto_vhr311lp">
                            <p xml:id="auto_bo05lifx">
                                <m>\textbf{v}</m> is Final velocity
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_4p3m3djg">
                            <p xml:id="auto_mhnv9i5q">
                                <m>\textbf{u}</m> is initial velocity
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_klguyusx">
                            <p xml:id="auto_csk607yp">
                                <m>\textbf{a}</m> is acceleration
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_5psa3cw6">
                            <p xml:id="auto_3qgr6kv7">
                                <m>\textbf{t}</m> is time
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
            </li> 
            <li xml:id="auto_39aybthh">    
                <p xml:id="auto_5fnj9t86">
                    <m>\text{Displacement}</m> = <m>(\text{initial velocity} \times \text{time}) + (\frac{1}{2} \times \text{acceleration} \times \text{time}^2) </m>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_nqmwkfvi">
                    <m> s = ut + \frac{1}{2} at^2 </m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_fc3pvhs1">    
                
                <p xml:id="auto_9qgfk9fk">
                    <m>\text{Final velocity}^2</m> = <m>\text{Initial velocity}^2</m> + (2 <m>\times</m> acceleration <m>\times</m> displacement)
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_ih8iv2l9">
                    <m>\textbf{v}^2 = \textbf{u}^2 + \, (2 \times \textbf{acceleration}) \times \textbf{s}^2</m>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
     <example xml:id="auto_7r51tqq3">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_ihxm0p6i">
                A car starts from rest and accelerates at 2 m/s² for 5 seconds. Find its final velocity.
            </p>
        </statement>    
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_prjm3xmz">
                <m> v = u + at  </m>
            </p>  
            <p xml:id="auto_kinl36rk">
                <m>= 0 + (2 \times 5) = 10 \textbf{ m/s}</m>
            </p> 
            <p xml:id="auto_covd04mc">
                The final velocity is <m>10 \textbf{ m/s}</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example xml:id="auto_x5b3mdje">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_0smtw0yu">
                A rocket accelerates from rest to <m>\textbf{250 m/s in 10 seconds}</m>. Calculate the rocket's acceleration.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_qp2a12lj">
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(u) = 0 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_jrc0azwj">
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 250 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_u0ox1eqy">
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{10 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_s1di0myv">
                Acceleration (a) = (v - u) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - u)}}{\textbf{t}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_j3edz8e7">
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s - 0 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_cjy15jkb">
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(250 m/s)}}{\textbf{10 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_zi7h8ske">
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = 25 m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_eif274rx">
                The rocket's acceleration is <m>\textbf{25 m/s²}</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example xml:id="auto_e7k2g744">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_x04wk05q">
                An object decelerates from 20 m/s to 5 m/s in 3 seconds. What is its acceleration?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_2d7veccb">
                Initial velocity  <m>\textbf{(u) = 20 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_mc9n4lhe">
                Final velocity  <m>\textbf{(v) = 5 m/s}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_52nyws1i">
                Time (t) = <m>\textbf{3 seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_16rrr350">
                Acceleration (a) = (v - u) / t
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{\textbf{(v - u)}}{t} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_mevskiyd">
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(5 m/s - 20 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_fh2ww80z">
                <md>
                    <mrow> a = \frac{\textbf{(-15 m/s)}}{\textbf{3 seconds}}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_q5hrreyw">
                <md>
                    <mrow>\textbf{ a = -5 m/s²}</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_zah2icrd">
                The object's acceleration is  <m>\textbf{ -5 m/s²}</m>. The negative sign indicates deceleration (slowing down).
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
